 {"id":"remote_compilation_helper-i6x","title":"Task: Worker Telemetry Collection Agent (Network Metrics)","description":"## Overview
Implement network metrics collection for worker telemetry, reading from /proc/net/dev to track bandwidth utilization and network health for rsync transfers.

## Background and Justification
Network bandwidth affects RCH performance significantly:
- rsync file synchronization consumes upstream/downstream bandwidth
- Workers on slow networks increase total build time
- Network saturation can cause SSH timeouts and build failures

## Implementation Details

### Data Sources (Linux)
```rust
// Read from /proc/net/dev
// Format: Interface | bytes packets errs drop ... | bytes packets errs drop ...
//         eth0:  1234567890   12345    0    0 ...   987654321   9876    0    0 ...

pub struct NetDevStats {
    pub interface: String,
    pub rx_bytes: u64,
    pub rx_packets: u64,
    pub rx_errors: u64,
    pub rx_dropped: u64,
    pub tx_bytes: u64,
    pub tx_packets: u64,
    pub tx_errors: u64,
    pub tx_dropped: u64,
}

// Derived metrics from deltas
pub struct NetworkMetrics {
    pub rx_throughput_mbps: f64,      // (rx_bytes_delta * 8) / (elapsed_ms * 1000)
    pub tx_throughput_mbps: f64,      // (tx_bytes_delta * 8) / (elapsed_ms * 1000)
    pub rx_packets_per_sec: f64,
    pub tx_packets_per_sec: f64,
    pub error_rate: f64,              // (rx_errors + tx_errors) / total_packets
    pub drop_rate: f64,               // (rx_dropped + tx_dropped) / total_packets
}
```

### Interface Filtering
```rust
// Filter to physical interfaces, exclude:
// - lo (loopback)
// - docker*, veth* (container networking)
// - virbr* (libvirt bridges)

fn is_physical_interface(name: &str) -> bool {
    !name.starts_with("lo") &&
    !name.starts_with("docker") &&
    !name.starts_with("veth") &&
    !name.starts_with("virbr") &&
    !name.starts_with("br-")
}
```

### Connection Quality Metrics
```rust
// Optional: TCP connection stats from /proc/net/tcp
pub struct TcpStats {
    pub retransmit_rate: f64,  // Indicates network quality
    pub connection_count: u32,
}
```

## Test Requirements

### Unit Tests
```rust
#[test]
fn test_parse_net_dev() {
    info!("TEST START: test_parse_net_dev");
    let line = "  eth0: 1234567890 12345 0 0 0 0 0 0  987654321 9876 0 0 0 0 0 0";
    info!("INPUT: /proc/net/dev line: {}", line);
    let stats = parse_net_dev_line(line).unwrap();
    info!("RESULT: NetDevStats {{ interface: {}, rx_bytes: {}, tx_bytes: {} }}", 
          stats.interface, stats.rx_bytes, stats.tx_bytes);
    assert_eq!(stats.interface, "eth0");
    assert_eq!(stats.rx_bytes, 1234567890);
    info!("VERIFY: eth0 parsed with correct byte counts");
    info!("TEST PASS: test_parse_net_dev");
}

#[test]
fn test_calculate_throughput() {
    info!("TEST START: test_calculate_throughput");
    let prev_bytes = 1_000_000_000u64;
    let curr_bytes = 1_125_000_000u64;
    let elapsed_ms = 1000;
    info!("INPUT: prev_bytes={}, curr_bytes={}, elapsed={}ms", prev_bytes, curr_bytes, elapsed_ms);
    let mbps = calculate_throughput_mbps(prev_bytes, curr_bytes, elapsed_ms);
    info!("RESULT: throughput = {} Mbps", mbps);
    assert!((mbps - 1000.0).abs() < 0.01);  // 125MB/s = 1000 Mbps
    info!("VERIFY: Expected 1000 Mbps, got {} Mbps", mbps);
    info!("TEST PASS: test_calculate_throughput");
}

#[test]
fn test_filter_physical_interfaces() {
    info!("TEST START: test_filter_physical_interfaces");
    let interfaces = vec!["eth0", "lo", "docker0", "veth1234", "ens192"];
    info!("INPUT: interfaces = {:?}", interfaces);
    let physical: Vec<_> = interfaces.iter().filter(|i| is_physical_interface(i)).collect();
    info!("RESULT: physical interfaces = {:?}", physical);
    assert_eq!(physical, vec![&"eth0", &"ens192"]);
    info!("VERIFY: Correctly filtered to eth0 and ens192");
    info!("TEST PASS: test_filter_physical_interfaces");
}
```

